                  </objectDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#24r" facs="025">Fol. 24r</locus>
                        <desc>
                           <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1071Cross">Cross</ref>, with the four letters for the word <term key="cross" ana="#cross"/>, <foreign xml:lang="gez">መስቀሉ፡</foreign>, on each of the arms of the <term key="cross" ana="#cross"/>. With caption <q>a rhyming poem from Canticle of the Flower is written around the cross. <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወኀበ፡ ተተክለ፡ ለዋሕድኪ፡ መስቀሉ፡ ሠራዊተ፡ ደዌ፡ ወሞት፡ ቀሪበ፡ ኢይክሉ፡</foreign>
                           </q>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d2">
                    Decorative designs:
                    <locus target="#1r" facs="002">fol. 1r</locus> (haräg);
                    the letter ተ, is used as section dividers throughout the codex. It is an abbreviation for <foreign xml:lang="gez">ተማኅፀንኩ፡</foreign>, “I beseech you.”
                    </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                          <locus target="#19r" facs="020"> f. 19r and passim</locus>
                           <desc type="OwnershipNote">names of three generations of owners are visible: the original owner’s first name was <foreign xml:lang="gez">ገብረ</foreign>፡, but the second name is erased; the name of one of the secondary owners was, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ገብረ፡ ሐይወት፡</foreign>; the other secondary owner, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወልደ፡ ማርያም፡</foreign>
                           </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                          <locus target="#ir(ecto) #iv(erso) #iir(ecto)" facs="001 002">Fols. ir(ecto), iv(erso), iir(ecto)</locus>
                           <desc>
                              blank
                            </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                          <locus target="#iiv(erso)" facs="003">Fol. iiv(erso)</locus>
